850
01:04:30,800 --> 01:04:34,240
It takes courage to be a human being.
It takes courage to be!

851
01:04:34,560 --> 01:04:39,560
Solitude is courage.
Hermetics. Total neutrality.

852
01:04:40,000 --> 01:04:45,800
To be unsure of yourself is courage.

853
01:04:46,360 --> 01:04:48,000
Courage is so many things.

854
01:04:48,160 --> 01:04:51,160
Courage is the courage
of Aung San Suu Kyi,

855
01:04:51,800 --> 01:04:54,120
who is being kept

856
01:04:55,400 --> 01:04:58,400
incommunicado
and under house arrest.

857
01:04:58,800 --> 01:05:02,000
Courage is the courage of

858
01:05:02,160 --> 01:05:06,160
the young students
in Tiananmen Square.

859
01:05:06,320 --> 01:05:10,720
We risk our lives
in many different ways.

860
01:05:10,880 --> 01:05:13,640
I've never really risked mine,
so I can't say.

861
01:05:13,960 --> 01:05:17,000
I've never lived
in truly dangerous situations.

862
01:05:17,320 --> 01:05:20,400
The way so many people
around this table have done.

863
01:05:20,720 --> 01:05:23,120
To put it simply,
to be willing to die.

864
01:05:23,280 --> 01:05:25,080
Yes, to be willing to die.

865
01:05:25,240 --> 01:05:28,240
To have the courage
to take the risk to die,

866
01:05:28,400 --> 01:05:31,160
to defend who I am and what I'm doing.

867
01:05:33,000 --> 01:05:35,320
Well, I mean,
we're sitting in a square,

868
01:05:35,480 --> 01:05:39,800
where the adventure of Nazism

869
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:44,560
took over
this beautiful country of Germany,

870
01:05:44,880 --> 01:05:47,880
and distorted the laws of justice

871
01:05:48,400 --> 01:05:51,400
in a most gross and horrific fashion.

872
01:05:51,960 --> 01:05:55,720
Imagine the courage of people
that broke the laws of the state

873
01:05:56,040 --> 01:05:59,040
to honour the higher law

874
01:05:59,200 --> 01:06:03,200
of caring for human life.

875
01:06:05,400 --> 01:06:08,880
You don't know
that Chinese prison labour camps

876
01:06:09,040 --> 01:06:11,240
are similar to Soviet gulags,

877
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:14,000
or German concentration camps.

878
01:06:14,160 --> 01:06:17,800
About 40 or 50 million people
lost their lives there.

879
01:06:19,000 --> 01:06:21,000
I was there for 19 years,

880
01:06:22,000 --> 01:06:25,000
before I made it to America.

881
01:06:25,160 --> 01:06:27,560
I didn't want to talk about this,

882
01:06:28,160 --> 01:06:30,160
but finally I have,

883
01:06:31,560 --> 01:06:34,040
because we have only one lifetime.

884
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:37,800
What would Argentina have been
without the courage

885
01:06:38,120 --> 01:06:40,080
of the Mothers of the Plaza de Mayo,

886
01:06:40,400 --> 01:06:43,080
who stood up to the dictatorships
and terrorism

887
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:46,240
of the Generals Videla,
Massera and Agosti,

888
01:06:46,400 --> 01:06:50,400
who "disappeared" thousands of people
by throwing them into the sea.

889
01:06:50,560 --> 01:06:52,400
What would have become of us

890
01:06:52,560 --> 01:06:55,280
without the lesson in courage
taught by these mothers,

891
01:06:55,440 --> 01:06:58,840
who stood before the Casa de Gobierno
every Thursday

892
01:06:59,000 --> 01:07:02,760
with the portraits
of their disappeared sons?

893
01:07:03,080 --> 01:07:05,080
Courage means to understand

894
01:07:05,240 --> 01:07:08,680
that these powers are not invincible,

895
01:07:09,240 --> 01:07:12,240
as is being demonstrated
by people in the world,

896
01:07:12,480 --> 01:07:14,960
who, with courage and indignation,

897
01:07:15,960 --> 01:07:19,840
have managed to expel
transnationals from their countries,

898
01:07:20,000 --> 01:07:21,800
have managed to overthrow

899
01:07:21,960 --> 01:07:24,960
and topple governments.

900
01:07:25,920 --> 01:07:28,240
Courage has everything to do with

901
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:31,640
looking at the future in the face,

902
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:36,240
always acknowledging
an element of the unknown,

903
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:41,400
but believing that if one sacrifices,

904
01:07:41,560 --> 01:07:43,160
if one suffers,

905
01:07:43,320 --> 01:07:47,560
if one takes a risk
and allows oneself to be vulnerable,

906
01:07:48,240 --> 01:07:51,240
that one can still make a difference.

907
01:07:51,840 --> 01:07:53,640
We should keep this in mind

908
01:07:53,800 --> 01:07:57,240
and it should make us
all the more radical and motivated,

909
01:07:57,560 --> 01:07:59,960
as we don't risk our lives,

910
01:08:00,280 --> 01:08:02,160
just a little boredom,

911
01:08:03,000 --> 01:08:06,200
a little ostracism,
a little of our well-being.

912
01:08:06,560 --> 01:08:10,040
Courage is also not just about
changing this world.

913
01:08:10,400 --> 01:08:12,640
It is really also about ensuring

914
01:08:12,800 --> 01:08:15,560
that the present day world
does not change me.

915
01:09:17,200 --> 01:09:18,760
Question 78.

916
01:09:19,640 --> 01:09:24,000
From Nancy Clemons, 57,
Cameron, Missouri, USA...

917
01:09:24,160 --> 01:09:29,160
"What can I do, and tell others to do,
to stop global warming?"

918
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:33,640
"What can I do, and tell others to do,
to stop global warming?"

919
01:09:33,800 --> 01:09:35,360
Please begin.

920
01:09:43,000 --> 01:09:46,480
This is a big question.

921
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:52,480
Quite simply, future generations
will not be able to understand

922
01:09:52,640 --> 01:09:56,640
our delirium of destruction.

923
01:09:58,560 --> 01:10:02,000
There's nothing we can do
to stop global warming.

924
01:10:02,160 --> 01:10:05,640
The ice is going to
carry on melting away.

925
01:10:06,400 --> 01:10:10,880
And now the question is:
Who will live?

926
01:10:11,400 --> 01:10:14,640
Who will live a life worth living?

927
01:10:15,280 --> 01:10:17,560
We know that many will perish.

928
01:10:19,400 --> 01:10:23,400
We know that many more
will barely survive with no life.

929
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:27,120
