01:16:35,400 --> 01:16:36,880
has only happened,

1008
01:16:37,040 --> 01:16:39,640
because we've also become
cut off from ourselves,

1009
01:16:39,800 --> 01:16:42,840
from our own hearts,
from our own bodies.

1010
01:16:43,000 --> 01:16:46,840
Nature makes the most sophisticated
materials on the planet

1011
01:16:47,000 --> 01:16:48,640
out of carbohydrates.

1012
01:16:48,800 --> 01:16:51,000
We too can learn how to do that.

1013
01:16:51,160 --> 01:16:55,120
But we have thought ourselves
to be superior to nature.

1014
01:16:55,440 --> 01:16:59,640
We haven't looked at her four and
a half billion years of experience

1015
01:16:59,800 --> 01:17:02,080
in incredible technologies.

1016
01:17:02,560 --> 01:17:04,240
Take a wasps' nest.

1017
01:17:04,400 --> 01:17:07,960
It's a building
that hangs from a single thread

1018
01:17:08,120 --> 01:17:11,080
made of material so light
that it can hold

1019
01:17:11,400 --> 01:17:14,840
three hundred times
its own weight in inhabitants.

1020
01:17:15,000 --> 01:17:18,000
Can we learn
to make buildings like that?

1021
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:22,840
Can we grow skyscrapers from
the bottom up the way a reed grows,

1022
01:17:23,000 --> 01:17:27,640
by building new cells at the bottom
of it and pushing itself upward?

1023
01:17:27,800 --> 01:17:30,200
We have so much to learn from nature.

1024
01:17:30,520 --> 01:17:34,400
It is by our own free choice,

1025
01:17:34,560 --> 01:17:37,560
by our personal efforts,

1026
01:17:37,720 --> 01:17:40,720
that we will achieve
balance with nature

1027
01:17:40,880 --> 01:17:43,840
and so become like all of nature.

1028
01:17:44,000 --> 01:17:45,640
Then we will feel

1029
01:17:45,800 --> 01:17:48,480
the eternity, perfection and harmony

1030
01:17:48,640 --> 01:17:51,640
that is everywhere in nature

1031
01:17:51,800 --> 01:17:56,800
except within our ourselves.

1032
01:17:57,000 --> 01:17:59,840
Everything we eat,
everything we wear,

1033
01:18:00,160 --> 01:18:04,160
all our houses, all our objects
come from the living Earth.

1034
01:18:04,400 --> 01:18:09,400
Learning how to live from that Earth
in a way that is sustainable

1035
01:18:09,560 --> 01:18:12,040
is not utopian, is not a dream.

1036
01:18:12,400 --> 01:18:16,640
What stands between us
and that possibility

1037
01:18:16,800 --> 01:18:19,400
is the idea that it can't be done,

1038
01:18:19,720 --> 01:18:22,640
the idea that they are too powerful,

1039
01:18:22,800 --> 01:18:25,240
that corporations can't change,

1040
01:18:25,400 --> 01:18:28,640
the idea
that people don't want change,

1041
01:18:28,800 --> 01:18:33,800
the idea that all of this comes
from innate human greed,

1042
01:18:33,960 --> 01:18:36,480
that it comes from overpopulation.

1043
01:18:36,640 --> 01:18:38,240
The planet is too crowded,

1044
01:18:38,560 --> 01:18:41,720
therefore it's not possible
to provide for people.

1045
01:18:42,040 --> 01:18:46,040
All of these are myths
that need to be reassessed,

1046
01:18:46,200 --> 01:18:48,840
assumptions that need to be rethought.

1047
01:19:39,160 --> 01:19:42,400
Question 96 comes from Miraj Khaled,

1048
01:19:43,000 --> 01:19:46,000
30, from Dhaka, Bangladesh.

1049
01:19:46,160 --> 01:19:49,160
"What is God's religion?", she asks.

1050
01:19:49,320 --> 01:19:51,760
"What is God's religion?"
Please begin.

1051
01:19:53,400 --> 01:19:56,240
I loved that question when I saw it,

1052
01:19:56,400 --> 01:19:59,320
because I think it's very perceptive.

1053
01:19:59,640 --> 01:20:02,040
Which God?

1054
01:20:04,000 --> 01:20:05,840
Which Religion?

1055
01:20:06,000 --> 01:20:08,000
What God? Whose God?

1056
01:20:10,400 --> 01:20:12,880
Whichever way we want to take it,

1057
01:20:13,800 --> 01:20:17,040
we must respect how others

1058
01:20:17,200 --> 01:20:20,200
see this word "God".

1059
01:20:21,000 --> 01:20:24,000
God is a way of defining

1060
01:20:24,160 --> 01:20:26,160
certain archetypes,

1061
01:20:26,320 --> 01:20:30,560
certain expectations

1062
01:20:31,400 --> 01:20:33,760
and objectives.

1063
01:20:34,800 --> 01:20:37,040
God is "is-ness".

1064
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:41,880
God is spirit. God is not religion.
God doesn't have a religion.

1065
01:20:43,160 --> 01:20:44,720
God doesn't exist.

1066
01:20:45,880 --> 01:20:48,440
The religion of my Goddess

1067
01:20:48,600 --> 01:20:52,080
is reflected
in every corner of the world,

1068
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:55,760
in every... leaf,

1069
01:20:56,080 --> 01:20:58,560
in every speck of dirt,

1070
01:20:58,720 --> 01:21:02,440
in every... flower.

1071
01:21:03,800 --> 01:21:06,640
No, I don't believe
that God has a religion.

1072
01:21:06,960 --> 01:21:12,440
I think that religion
is a profoundly human phenomenon.

1073
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:15,280
When we talk about
God having a religion,

1074
01:21:15,440 --> 01:21:16,920
you can rest assured

1075
01:21:17,080 --> 01:21:19,880
that we're talking about
some human construction,

1076
01:21:20,040 --> 01:21:21,800
some human creation.

1077
01:21:23,400 --> 01:21:26,840
What we project onto Him.

1078
01:21:27,160 --> 01:21:28,840
I am of Love.

1079
01:21:29,000 --> 01:21:30,760
I am of the Universe.

1080
01:21:30,920 --> 01:21:33,040
I am God in Action.

1081
01:21:33,200 --> 01:21:36,000
There is no God.

1082
01:21:36,160 --> 01:21:39,160
God is a symbol for something

1083
01:21:39,320 --> 01:21:41,800
that we can't express in words.

1084
01:21:42,400 --> 01:21:46,000
And that's also why
there's no God's religion.

1085
01:21:46,400 --> 01:21:50,000
God, we have to imagine, is something

1086
01:21:50,400 --> 01:21:52,640
that is not only unknown to us,

1087
01:21:52,800 --> 01:21:56,280
but is also beyond our knowledge,

1088
01:21:56,560 --> 01:21:59,840
that has no quality of being known.

1089
01:22:00,000 --> 01:22:03,400
It's as if
we were to ask the question,

1090
01:22:03,560 --> 01:22:07,200
what is the colour of a circle?

1091
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:11,160
Is it red, green or blue?

1092
01:22:11,480 --> 01:22:14,840
It's neither blue nor red nor green.

1093
01:22:15,000 --> 01:22:17,000
It's also not colourless.

1094
01:22:17,160 --> 01:22:21,640
The question about the colour
of the circle is absurd,

1095
01:22:21,800 --> 01:22:24,280
because a circle knows no colour.

1096
01:22:24,440 --> 01:22:26,840
Many people are unwilling to see this.

1097
01:22:27,000 --> 01:22:30,240
They take a pen out of their pocket,

1098
01:22:30,400 --> 01:22:32,400
draw a circle on a piece of paper

1099
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:35,400
and say, "Look, this circle is blue."

1100
01:22:35,720 --> 01:22:39,680
Yes, the circle drawn by them is blue,

1101
01:22:40,000 --> 01:22:42,840
but the colour comes from my pen,

1102
01:22:43,160 --> 01:22:45,000
and not from the circle.

1103
01:22:45,640 --> 01:22:48,640
The colour of the pen is the religion

1104
01:22:49,400 --> 01:22:52,400
with which we express the divinity,

1105
01:22:52,560 --> 01:22:55,560
but we cannot
draw the circle ourselves.

1106
01:22:55,720 --> 01:22:59,040
It is something
that has nothing to do with colours.

1107
01:22:59,360 --> 01:23:01,120
There are as many religions

1108
01:23:01,280 --> 01:23:04,360
as there are colours
with which I can draw a circle.

1109
01:23:07,000 --> 01:23:09,000
I really like that one.

1110
01:23:10,880 --> 01:23:13,720
I believe in God,
but all I know about God is,

1111
01:23:14,040 --> 01:23:16,200
there is a God and it isn't me.

1112
01:23:16,360 --> 01:23:17,840
That's all I know so far.

1113
01:23:18,200 --> 01:23:20,240
Don't you think
God is in you as well?

1114
01:23:20,560 --> 01:23:22,560
Oh absolutely. Absolutely.

1115
01:23:22,720 --> 01:23:26,400
Most of my whole thing
with spirituality is...

1116
01:23:26,560 --> 01:23:28,600
I'm a recovering heroin addict.

1117
01:23:29,000 --> 01:23:31,480
I haven't met God yet.

1118
01:23:32,160 --> 01:23:35,400
If I meet Him one day,

1119
01:23:35,800 --> 01:23:39,280
then I will ask Him the questions.

1120
01:24:24,800 --> 01:24:27,680
-Thank you.
-Thank you, too.

1121
01:24:28,400 --> 01:24:30,320
-Last one.
-Question...

1122
01:24:34,720 --> 01:24:36,320
-100!
-100.

1123
01:24:42,240 --> 01:24:45,200
-Last one.
-I didn't think we'd make it!

1124
01:24:58,400 --> 01:25:00,480
Okay, last question. Let's do it.

1125
01:25:01,000 --> 01:25:06,800
From Keith Dierkx, 48,
Piedmont, California, USA.

1126
01:25:07,160 --> 01:25:09,640
"What are the myths
that we need to create"

1127
01:25:09,800 --> 01:25:12,200
"to change the world for the better?"

1128
01:25:13,160 --> 01:25:17,160
Creation stories are part of every
culture in human history,

1129
01:25:17,320 --> 01:25:21,120
and they were usually told
by some kind of a priesthood.

1130
01:25:21,440 --> 01:25:23,760
But now science
tells the creation story.

1131
01:25:24,080 --> 01:25:27,080
It has been elevated
to that status of priesthood

1132
01:25:27,240 --> 01:25:30,240
that gets to tell
the big story to the culture.

1133
01:25:30,400 --> 01:25:32,400
What story is it telling us?

1134
01:25:32,560 --> 01:25:36,240
That we live in a non-living,
purposeless universe

1135
01:25:36,400 --> 01:25:38,240
running down by entropy.

1136
01:25:38,400 --> 01:25:41,880
Oh! How cheery is that
for a creation story?

1137
01:25:42,040 --> 01:25:45,680
And then we add in
that evolution on this planet

1138
01:25:46,000 --> 01:25:48,480
is about the survival of the fittest,

1139
01:25:48,800 --> 01:25:52,520
about an endless competition
in scarcity,

1140
01:25:52,840 --> 01:25:55,680
and that you have to get
what you can while you can

1141
01:25:56,000 --> 01:25:57,840
and beat the other guy to it.

1142
01:25:58,000 --> 01:26:01,000
This is a totally depressing
creation story,

1143
01:26:01,160 --> 01:26:03,760
a universe running down meaninglessly,

1144
01:26:04,080 --> 01:26:07,640
you're stuck
in an endless struggle in scarcity.

1145
01:26:07,800 --> 01:26:13,040
This is a terrible story to tell.
It doesn't fit the scientific facts.

1146
01:26:13,200 --> 01:26:15,920
Every force in nature has an opposite.

1147
01:26:16,240 --> 01:26:19,160
If there's entropy,
there has to be syntropy.

1148
01:26:19,480 --> 01:26:23,480
In evolution there's a tremendous
amount of cooperation.

1149
01:26:23,640 --> 01:26:26,640
In fact, I'd say there's a great story

1150
01:26:26,800 --> 01:26:30,200
in the maturation cycle
of evolving species,

1151
01:26:30,360 --> 01:26:32,920
where they first are young and grabby

1152
01:26:33,240 --> 01:26:36,240
they multiply
and take all the territory they can,

1153
01:26:36,400 --> 01:26:39,640
bump off their competitors,
act like capitalists.

1154
01:26:39,800 --> 01:26:44,280
And then they discover, bit by bit,
the advantages of cooperation.

1155
01:26:44,440 --> 01:26:50,000
And, as they do so, they build bigger
and bigger cooperative enterprises

1156
01:26:50,160 --> 01:26:52,680
and find out
that their economies are cheaper,

1157
01:26:52,840 --> 01:26:55,840
more effective, more efficient,
work for everybody,

1158
01:26:56,000 --> 01:26:58,520
and you get
the evolution of rainforests,

1159
01:26:58,680 --> 01:27:01,680
and human bodies
made of a hundred trillion cells,

1160
01:27:01,840 --> 01:27:06,080
working in complete cooperation
even though they're so diverse.

1161
01:27:06,240 --> 01:27:10,240
This is a story we need to tell
in the world, a great new story

1162
01:27:10,400 --> 01:27:14,400
of the human species
growing up into global family,

1163
01:27:14,560 --> 01:27:18,800
doing win-win economics
and making a better world for all.

1164
01:27:19,120 --> 01:27:23,120
Human beings are appreciators,

1165
01:27:23,560 --> 01:27:27,800
not just observers
but appreciators, participants,

1166
01:27:28,080 --> 01:27:31,000
even co-creators
of the cosmic process.

1167
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:36,800
The whole world is deeply entangled.

1168
01:27:37,160 --> 01:27:41,840
All the living organisms,
all the parts of the universe.

1169
01:27:42,000 --> 01:27:44,000
The whole universe is living,

1170
01:27:44,160 --> 01:27:47,240
the electrons
and the protons and everything.

1171
01:27:47,560 --> 01:27:49,240
They are all organisms.

1172
01:27:49,400 --> 01:27:54,400
They all have a history
and they are all entangled so deeply,

1173
01:27:54,560 --> 01:27:59,040
intimately interconnected,
that you cannot separate them.

1174
01:27:59,360 --> 01:28:03,840
And, at any moment,
this entangled universe

1175
01:28:04,000 --> 01:28:07,840
is creating
and recreating itself anew.

1176
01:28:08,000 --> 01:28:11,000
That, I think,
is the evolution of the cosmos,

1177
01:28:11,160 --> 01:28:16,640
the evolution of all things in it
from atoms, to humans, to galaxies.

1178
01:28:17,000 --> 01:28:20,280
That is the objective.
That is the ambition.

1179
01:28:21,000 --> 01:28:24,400
That is the ultimate aim
of divine creativity.

1180
01:28:24,560 --> 01:28:28,800
That's as far as we can come
as human beings to understand it.

1181
01:28:31,000 --> 01:28:32,560
I believe

1182
01:28:34,160 --> 01:28:38,040
in a measure of humility,

1183
01:28:39,000 --> 01:28:42,480
and in a measure of humanity,

1184
01:28:43,840 --> 01:28:46,280
and in an avowal of beauty

1185
01:28:46,600 --> 01:28:48,840
as an antidote to all the brutality,

1186
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:51,000
and cruelty of the world.

1187
01:28:52,000 --> 01:28:53,560
I believe

1188
01:28:54,200 --> 01:28:56,440
that the sacred lives in nature,

1189
01:28:56,600 --> 01:28:58,600
not only in the supernatural,

1190
01:28:58,800 --> 01:29:01,200
but also in the beauty of nature.

1191
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:03,080
I believe

1192
01:29:03,800 --> 01:29:06,040
human beings
are metaphysical animals,

1193
01:29:06,200 --> 01:29:08,680
and always will be
because of their mortality.

1194
01:29:08,840 --> 01:29:11,840
The human is the only animal
that knows it must die.

1195
01:29:12,000 --> 01:29:14,240
This is the source of the mystery,

1196
01:29:14,400 --> 01:29:17,400
of the unending mystery
of human existence.

1197
01:29:17,800 --> 01:29:22,800
It would have to do
with the marrying of the mind,

1198
01:29:24,080 --> 01:29:28,200
the soul,
and this corporeal little covering

1199
01:29:28,520 --> 01:29:30,520
that is supposed to be the body.

1200
01:29:32,400 --> 01:29:34,880
The marriage of all those,

1201
01:29:35,200 --> 01:29:38,640
if it indeed be that,

1202
01:29:38,800 --> 01:29:41,200
can only be powered by positivity.

1203
01:29:41,520 --> 01:29:43,840
And if the positivity

1204
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:47,560
then manages
to give birth to that marriage...

1205
01:29:48,160 --> 01:29:51,640
then all the troubles of the Earth
will be gone.

1206
01:29:51,800 --> 01:29:54,080
If the human mind has got the space

1207
01:29:54,240 --> 01:29:59,240
in which to breathe,
to live, to pulse, to flow...

1208
01:30:19,080 --> 01:30:24,080
Who is ever going
to listen to all of this?

1209
01:30:24,400 --> 01:30:28,640
Because we're one hundred and twelve,
there are a hundred questions.

1210
01:30:29,000 --> 01:30:33,000
That's 11,200. Let's say...

1211
01:30:34,000 --> 01:30:38,000
Only two minutes each time.
That's 22,000 minutes.

1212
01:30:38,160 --> 01:30:40,160
You know what that is?

1213
01:30:41,240 --> 01:30:44,240
That's three hundred days.

1214
01:30:47,000 --> 01:30:48,880
Okay, we're finished.

1215
01:30:49,400 --> 01:30:51,400
It's over.

